THE eagerly awaited Bafana Bafana’s Africa Nations Cup 2021 qualifiers against Ghana and Sudan have been rescheduled.Bafana will now take on Ghana’s Black Stars on 14 November instead of the following day as it was previously scheduled by Caf who initially changed the dates for the continental showpiece qualifiers.South Africa will then host Sudan three days later at Orlando Stadium.Molefi Ntseki’s charges are in Group C together with the Black Stars, Sudan and Sao Tome Principe.Two teams from the Group will qualify for Afcon 2021 finals in Cameroon.Sao Tome registered a historic victory over Mauritius as they thrashed them 3-1 in the first leg of the preliminary round and followed it up with a 2-1 victory in the second leg to complete a remarkable 5-2 aggregate win. 